<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-19T23:40:00-05:00" n="370" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1905-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1905-12-20T00:00:00-04:40">undated</date>]. [<hi rend="italic">Received December 29,
                            1905</hi>].</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Gunboat <hi rend="italic">Independencia</hi> sent by Cabinet to Sanchez
                            with munitions has deserted and gone to Monte Christi. Will probably
                            bring expedition against Macoris or other point. Whereabouts of the
                            President unknown. The Vice-President arrives here to-day. French chargé
                            d’affaires offers, if agreeable to the American Government, to send
                            Martinique for war ship to aid in protecting lives foreigners which
                            might be endangered by landing American seamen.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>